channel.title: What Should I Get?
channel.description:
Well for Christmas, I usually get a variety off things. (Money, clothes, other items)
I have a choice wether I can get either an iPhone 4S, or a new laptop.
Laptop; my current laptop is doing perfectly fine, just a tad bit slow.
Phone: I have a Blackjack, if you don't know what that is, it's basically a blackberry but way less technologically advanced.
So, iPhone or laptop?

item.description:
@Kidpaparoach wrote:

I had the iPhone 3G which was mince but the new iPhone 4S + iPhone 4 are really good but are based on really unstable systems apparently(hence all the problems).
In my opinion do what that guy(sell laptop you’ve currently got + get new laptop + buy phone with money from selling old) said buuut get a Computer cause your budget doesn’t seem too huge.
Phones wise, iphones look smexi and are good for apps so its more like a sign of wealth in a sense?
Blackberry’s are utterly crap(curve’s are cheap) but on the positive side looads of people(mostly girls:D) have blackberry messenger and they add you = amazing way to chat up and meet new people which is the only reason I still have mines lolol. So maybe get a blackberry + ipod touch?

item.title: What Should I Get?
item.dc:creator: @davidi2 Davidi2
item.description:
@davidi2 wrote:

Invest it in Au (I don’t say gold or people will think I mean RSGP… though now that I think about it, that would probably go up too) or something similar. If you have a laptop that works fine, why would you need another one? If you don’t have a phone I guess go for that if you don’t feel like being charitable or anything, but like people before said, they’re all going to be outdated in a year anyway. If it was me, I’d ask for the laptop and give mine away or something… 'tis the season after all.

Personally I don’t have my own laptop OR a phone (well thats a bit of an exaggeration, I have a phone but it’s nothing special. Like a 19 dollar phone without a contract :rolleyes:), and it’s not because we’re poor or anything (I’ve got like 40k in stocks and bonds from my parents and grandparents for college/a house when I’m older). I always invest 20% of my gifts, 10% goes to my church, 10% into savings (for big things), 10% goes to charity, and 50% for pocket cash.

Though I guess I could ask the same question as you, I got my summer job paycheck and after I split the rest up, I still have like $500 pocket cash to spend now, not sure what to do with it…
